            "answer_text": "My high school computer science teacher had an interesting way. We wrote our mid-term supervised by a teacher who wasn\u2019t our computer science teacher, and wasn\u2019t familiar with the poorest students who were also frequent absentees. He was, therefore, a bit easier to fool. This was just before the Christmas break. We came back in January and our computer science teacher walked in and said: \u201cBad news guys. I lost your exams. You have to rewrite them.\u201d He had 30 blank exam papers with him and we acquiesced and rewrote our answers. It was the same exam we\u2019d written in December. After 90 minutes of exam writing he collected our papers and told us: \u201cI had a feeling that two of you cheated on the mid-term. I wanted to use this as a way of proving it. I would never lose your exams.\u201d He never did tell us if the two had cheated or not, but I suspect he caught the cheaters. ",
