                "name": "Noel Walker",
                "href": "/profile/Noel-Walker-18"
            },
            "answer_text": "First off, when students cheat and get away with it, they typically repeat that behavior. So don\u2019t worry if you think they did it in the past and got away with it- let that one go. Instead, prepare to catch them in the act next time. And how do you do that? Give them different versions of the same test. Don\u2019t make the tests wildly different, instead, make them slightly different so that the questions appear pretty much the same, but the answers should be very different. And then just see how they do on it. If they cheat, you\u2019ll hopefully be able to tell. ",
            "date": "Answered March 25, 2018",
            "views": "724",
            "upvotes": "0"
        },
